# VMware Workstation Setup

VMware Workstation is a desktop virtualization software that allows multiple operating systems to run simultaneously on a single physical computer. It provides an isolated environment for testing, development, and learning without affecting the host operating system.

In this project, VMware Workstation is used to build a Red Hat High Availability (HA) Cluster by creating multiple Red Hat Enterprise Linux virtual machines.

---

# Lab Requirements

| Component | Requirement |
|-----------|-------------|
| Host OS | Windows 10/11 (64-bit) |
| Hypervisor | VMware Workstation Pro |
| Guest OS | Red Hat Enterprise Linux 9 |
| CPU | Intel VT-x / AMD-V Supported |
| RAM | Minimum 12 GB (16 GB Recommended) |
| Disk Space | 80 GB Free |

